Indonesia Stocks: Bakrie & Brothers, Garuda Indonesia, Timah

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-31T09:12:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/indonesia-stocks-bakrie-brothers-mandiri-united-tractors.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  climbed 37.70 points, or 1
percent, to 3,678.67, the highest close since Jan. 6. The gauge
fell 0.7 percent this quarter, the first decline since the three
months ended Dec. 31, 2008.  PT Bakrie & Brothers (BNBR IJ), an  investment company , fell
3 percent to 64 rupiah. Bakrie & Brothers’ 2010 net loss widened
to 7.64 trillion rupiah ($877 million) from 1.74 trillion rupiah
a year earlier, it said in a statement published in Investor
Daily Indonesia.  PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI IJ), the nation’s largest bank by
assets, gained 4.6 percent to 6,800 rupiah. The company’s 2010
net income rose 29 percent from a year earlier to 9.22 trillion
rupiah, it said in a statement. A survey of 23 analysts by
Bloomberg estimated net income of 8.8 trillion rupiah for the
full year. Bank Mandiri,  PT Bank Rakyat  Indonesia  (BBRI IJ), the nation’s second-
biggest bank by assets, increased 6.5 percent to 5,750 rupiah,
the steepest gain since March 4. The bank’s 2010 net income
jumped 58 percent from a year earlier to 11.5 trillion rupiah,
it said in a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia . That
compares with the average estimate of 9.2 trillion rupiah of 25
analysts in a Bloomberg News survey.  PT Garuda Indonesia (GIAA IJ), the nation’s largest
airline, fell 3.6 percent to 530 rupiah. The company’s 2010 net
income declined to 515.5 billion rupiah from 1 trillion rupiah a
year earlier, it said in a stock exchange filing.  PT Timah (TINS IJ), Indonesia’s biggest tin producer, rose
6.7 percent to 2,775 rupiah, the sharpest gain since Sept. 30.
The company’s 2010 net income surged to 948 billion rupiah from
313.8 billion rupiah a year earlier, the company said in a
statement to the stock exchange. A survey of eight analysts by
Bloomberg estimated net income of 763.4 billion rupiah for the
full year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
